1
00:00:17,832 --> 00:00:19,124
[alarm beeps]

2
00:00:21,001 --> 00:00:23,212
[theme music playing]

3
00:00:59,707 --> 00:01:00,541
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

4
00:01:00,624 --> 00:01:02,126
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED SAFELY
WITH SUPERVISION

5
00:01:02,710 --> 00:01:04,712
[sibling] How was your last relationship?

6
00:01:05,838 --> 00:01:06,881
[chuckles] It was a failure.

7
00:01:08,340 --> 00:01:11,051
Still though,
I learned a few things from it.

8
00:01:11,135 --> 00:01:12,261
YOON DA-RA
WEB NOVEL WRITER

9
00:01:12,344 --> 00:01:13,429
What kind of things did you learn?

10
00:01:13,512 --> 00:01:17,099
"Don't fool yourself into thinking that
love can change a person."

11
00:01:17,182 --> 00:01:19,935
So, how come you even considered
getting married?

12
00:01:20,019 --> 00:01:22,605
I fooled myself into thinking

13
00:01:22,688 --> 00:01:24,523
that marriage would
solve all our problems.

14
00:01:24,607 --> 00:01:26,942
That he would completely
become "my person."

15
00:01:27,443 --> 00:01:29,320
And I'd be able to escape
from my loneliness.

16
00:01:29,403 --> 00:01:31,530
What type of person
would you like to date next?

17
00:01:31,614 --> 00:01:33,324
Someone more grounded.

18
00:01:34,491 --> 00:01:35,784
And that I don't have to babysit.

19
00:01:37,786 --> 00:01:39,747
[Da-ra] Would you say
you're the grounded type?

20
00:01:39,830 --> 00:01:40,831
Yes.

21
00:01:40,915 --> 00:01:43,042
By the way, why are you still standing?

22
00:01:43,125 --> 00:01:44,710
I didn't get a chance to work out today.

23
00:01:44,793 --> 00:01:46,253
Oh, I see.

24
00:01:46,337 --> 00:01:47,588
You're not married, right?

25
00:01:47,671 --> 00:01:48,589
Actually, I'm divorced.

26
00:01:48,672 --> 00:01:49,590
Huh?

27
00:01:53,761 --> 00:01:58,057
Then how do you think that experience
affected your next relationship?

28
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:02,978
I guess it left me with a fear of love.

29
00:02:03,062 --> 00:02:05,189
Will you ever give love another try?

30
00:02:05,773 --> 00:02:07,358
-[smacks lips]
-[sighs]

31
00:02:08,484 --> 00:02:09,443
-I'm not sure.
-I'm not sure.

32
00:02:11,737 --> 00:02:12,738
[romantic music playing]

33
00:02:12,821 --> 00:02:13,864
[Si-woo] I like you.

34
00:02:15,199 --> 00:02:16,450
[Ji-yoon] I like you too.

35
00:02:22,331 --> 00:02:23,707
In the beginning,

36
00:02:23,791 --> 00:02:25,834
you're convinced everything will go well.

37
00:02:27,878 --> 00:02:29,546
You picture only the good stuff

38
00:02:29,630 --> 00:02:31,632
rather than the hardships.

39
00:02:33,467 --> 00:02:35,344
I'm probably fooling myself again.

40
00:02:35,427 --> 00:02:36,553
That's for sure.

41
00:02:37,721 --> 00:02:39,056
But what can I do?

42
00:02:40,015 --> 00:02:42,977
Starting all over again.
That's the magic of love.

43
00:02:43,060 --> 00:02:49,608
EPISODE 7 HAVE A NEW SECRET,
STILL CLOCKING IN!

44
00:02:56,156 --> 00:02:58,158
[panting]

45
00:03:03,789 --> 00:03:04,790
[chuckles]

46
00:03:05,666 --> 00:03:07,543
[inhales deeply, exhales sharply]

47
00:03:08,460 --> 00:03:11,588
[phone alarm playing]

48
00:03:13,048 --> 00:03:14,174
[groans]

49
00:03:18,178 --> 00:03:19,555
[groans]

50
00:03:22,099 --> 00:03:23,392
ALARM

51
00:03:24,101 --> 00:03:25,436
[sighs]

52
00:03:26,937 --> 00:03:28,439
[phone chimes]

53
00:03:32,776 --> 00:03:33,777
[Si-woo] Good morning.

54
00:03:33,861 --> 00:03:36,989
[cheerful music playing]

55
00:03:37,072 --> 00:03:39,033
MANAGER KANG SI-WOO

56
00:03:39,116 --> 00:03:40,617
GOOD MORNING!

57
00:03:40,701 --> 00:03:41,702
[chuckles]

58
00:03:41,785 --> 00:03:43,746
A new relationship has begun.

59
00:03:45,831 --> 00:03:47,541
Why does my skin feel so rough?

60
00:03:49,501 --> 00:03:50,627
No, this won't do.

61
00:03:55,841 --> 00:03:58,218
After all, today is a special day.

62
00:04:04,475 --> 00:04:05,601
[sighs]

63
00:04:05,684 --> 00:04:06,685
[scoffs]

64
00:04:07,436 --> 00:04:10,355
Smooth as a baby's bottom. [chuckles]

65
00:04:22,659 --> 00:04:23,619
[giggles]

66
00:04:28,832 --> 00:04:30,292
I'm sorry
that you missed your morning run.

67
00:04:30,375 --> 00:04:31,418
I did run.

68
00:04:32,377 --> 00:04:33,629
But it's only 7:30 a.m.

69
00:04:33,712 --> 00:04:34,838
I woke up at 5:00.

70
00:04:34,922 --> 00:04:36,673
Wow. [chuckles]

71
00:04:40,302 --> 00:04:41,428
What is all this for?

72
00:04:41,512 --> 00:04:44,473
I got you some red ginseng
for your immune system,

73
00:04:44,556 --> 00:04:46,517
and also, women's health supplements.

74
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,310
Set an alarm to take them every day.

75
00:04:48,393 --> 00:04:49,561
[chuckles]

76
00:04:50,270 --> 00:04:51,355
Thank you.

77
00:05:02,241 --> 00:05:04,743
Because today is a day worth celebrating.

78
00:05:09,665 --> 00:05:11,125
You should've left the flowers at home.

79
00:05:12,334 --> 00:05:14,753
I'm going to put them on my desk
and look at them all day.

80
00:05:16,755 --> 00:05:18,507
How should we go about it at work?

81
00:05:19,133 --> 00:05:21,468
I think it's best we keep it a secret.

82
00:05:21,969 --> 00:05:23,470
Why?

83
00:05:23,554 --> 00:05:25,639
Well, if people find out about us,

84
00:05:25,722 --> 00:05:28,142
they won't see us
as a boss and a subordinate anymore.

85
00:05:28,225 --> 00:05:31,270
They may say,
"Are they here to work or date?"

86
00:05:31,353 --> 00:05:32,896
Or they'll whisper, "Did they fight?"

87
00:05:33,897 --> 00:05:35,649
Whether you compliment me or tell me off,

88
00:05:35,732 --> 00:05:37,860
they'll always view it
with some prejudice.

89
00:05:38,443 --> 00:05:40,821
I don't want to have to walk
on eggshells at work.

90
00:05:40,904 --> 00:05:43,866
Once there's a secret,
we'll have to tell that many more lies.

91
00:05:44,449 --> 00:05:45,868
Well, I'm a good liar.

92
00:05:47,035 --> 00:05:49,163
I managed to hide my feelings for you
pretty well, didn't I?

93
00:05:49,788 --> 00:05:50,622
Did you now?

94
00:05:50,706 --> 00:05:52,457
[scoffs] Wait. Did it show?

95
00:05:52,541 --> 00:05:54,751
Let's keep it a secret
as you want, Ji-yoon.

96
00:05:57,171 --> 00:05:58,297
"Ji-yoon."

97
00:05:58,380 --> 00:06:00,215
I really like it when you call me that.

98
00:06:00,299 --> 00:06:02,926
Okay, then.
And would you call me the same way?

99
00:06:03,010 --> 00:06:05,804
-[Ji-yoon] "Si-woo"?
-[record scratch plays]

100
00:06:05,888 --> 00:06:07,890
I think I'll need
a little bit more time for that.

101
00:06:08,599 --> 00:06:09,600
[chuckles]

102
00:06:10,267 --> 00:06:12,978
[gasps] Oh.
You can drop me off right there.

103
00:06:14,062 --> 00:06:15,689
Why? There's still a long way to go.

104
00:06:15,772 --> 00:06:18,775
[sighs] Do you think you could be
a tad more discreet, Mr. Kang?

105
00:06:18,859 --> 00:06:20,068
[chuckles]

106
00:06:24,364 --> 00:06:25,991
[Ji-yoon] Here's how it goes at an office.

107
00:06:26,074 --> 00:06:28,702
[upbeat music playing]

108
00:06:28,785 --> 00:06:30,746
You'll be joining us
for lunch today, right?

109
00:06:33,290 --> 00:06:35,959
Or should we make an excuse
to sneak off together?

110
00:06:37,502 --> 00:06:38,503
I'm sorry.

111
00:06:39,296 --> 00:06:40,505
I still have some work to finish.

112
00:06:41,173 --> 00:06:42,090
You go ahead without me.

113
00:06:43,091 --> 00:06:44,134
[sighs]

114
00:06:44,801 --> 00:06:46,678
But I want to eat with you.

115
00:06:46,762 --> 00:06:49,640
Here even messages like this
are sent with a straight face,

116
00:06:49,723 --> 00:06:51,141
like it's just work.

117
00:06:51,934 --> 00:06:54,186
Mr. Kang, let's go for lunch.

118
00:06:54,811 --> 00:06:56,063
I'll be eating alone today.

119
00:06:56,146 --> 00:06:58,857
But it's been so nice
having you eat with us.

120
00:06:58,941 --> 00:07:00,067
Can you do it after lunch?

121
00:07:00,150 --> 00:07:02,653
Let's not bother Mr. Kang
and let him stay.

122
00:07:02,736 --> 00:07:03,737
Okay.

123
00:07:04,947 --> 00:07:06,990
[Ji-yoon] So nothing's really changed
between us.

124
00:07:07,074 --> 00:07:09,243
-Well, then we'll head out for lunch.
-[Si-woo] Okay.

125
00:07:10,869 --> 00:07:13,789
[playful music playing]

126
00:07:14,706 --> 00:07:16,500
[Ji-yoon] Well, maybe just a little.

127
00:07:16,583 --> 00:07:17,584
[chuckles]

128
00:07:23,465 --> 00:07:25,759
He doesn't wear a ring…

129
00:07:27,094 --> 00:07:29,471
so I don't think he's married.

130
00:07:30,347 --> 00:07:31,723
[gasps] A girlfriend?

131
00:07:31,807 --> 00:07:32,766
Who?

132
00:07:32,849 --> 00:07:33,725
Well, Mr. Kang.

133
00:07:33,809 --> 00:07:36,019
[No-ah scoffs]
He's practically at the office

134
00:07:36,103 --> 00:07:37,896
like built-in furniture.

135
00:07:37,980 --> 00:07:39,523
Do you know anything, Ms. Cha?

136
00:07:39,606 --> 00:07:40,691
Not really.

137
00:07:41,358 --> 00:07:42,943
I don't pay

138
00:07:43,735 --> 00:07:45,529
much attention to him, so…

139
00:07:46,113 --> 00:07:47,739
[sighs] Lie number one.

140
00:07:47,823 --> 00:07:49,116
Of course. [smacks lips]

141
00:07:49,199 --> 00:07:51,368
We have no romantic energy left,
so how could we know?

142
00:07:52,035 --> 00:07:53,036
Mmm. [chuckles]

143
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:55,122
Hmm? Come on.

144
00:07:55,747 --> 00:07:58,709
Our dear Ms. Cha is
dressed up so nicely today. Hmm?

145
00:07:58,792 --> 00:08:00,836
She even came in with flowers.

146
00:08:00,919 --> 00:08:01,795
What was with that?

147
00:08:01,878 --> 00:08:03,422
A special occasion today?

148
00:08:03,505 --> 00:08:04,548
No.

149
00:08:05,465 --> 00:08:08,135
I just thought I'd air it out
before it grew mold.

150
00:08:08,969 --> 00:08:12,556
And the flowers were
a spur-of-the-moment, uh, purchase.

151
00:08:12,639 --> 00:08:13,890
[Na-ri] Hmm.

152
00:08:14,891 --> 00:08:16,977
-You bought flowers for yourself?
-Hmm.

153
00:08:18,061 --> 00:08:20,397
That's really kinda sad, you know? Huh?

154
00:08:21,189 --> 00:08:22,190
Have some more meat.

155
00:08:22,816 --> 00:08:23,692
Here.

156
00:08:24,985 --> 00:08:27,029
You can have all of my tangsuyuk too.

157
00:08:27,654 --> 00:08:28,989
[Ji-yoon] I did it again. I lied.

158
00:08:29,072 --> 00:08:30,741
[Na-ri] You know
we're here for you, right?

159
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:33,035
We're back, sir.

160
00:08:41,293 --> 00:08:42,794
[Ji-yoon] I wonder if he's eaten.

161
00:08:42,878 --> 00:08:44,880
Mr. Kang, have you eaten already?

162
00:08:44,963 --> 00:08:46,173
No worries. I'll eat after the meeting.

163
00:08:46,798 --> 00:08:49,092
[Ji-yoon sighs]
He's going to pass out at this rate.

164
00:08:49,176 --> 00:08:53,055
I know work's important and all,
but you shouldn't skip meals.

165
00:08:53,722 --> 00:08:55,515
Here. A Dubai Chewy Cookie.

166
00:08:58,810 --> 00:08:59,686
Have one, Mr. Kang.

167
00:09:00,812 --> 00:09:02,856
[amusing music playing]

168
00:09:04,274 --> 00:09:06,818
Thank you, but I don't eat sweet things.
Someone else can have it.

169
00:09:06,902 --> 00:09:09,988
Oh, I love Dubai Chewy Cookies.
These are hard to get too.

170
00:09:10,072 --> 00:09:11,782
-I'll have that, thanks you.
-Wait!

171
00:09:11,865 --> 00:09:14,993
Do you know what I went through to get it?
You can't just take it.

172
00:09:15,952 --> 00:09:17,204
-[chuckles]
-[huffs]

173
00:09:17,287 --> 00:09:18,330
Let's start the meeting.

174
00:09:21,291 --> 00:09:23,001
[Na-ri] So unfair.

175
00:09:25,587 --> 00:09:29,174
In a month, we'll invite overseas buyers
and hold a Home-AI demonstration.

176
00:09:29,257 --> 00:09:31,301
We'll do a demonstration in a month?

177
00:09:31,385 --> 00:09:32,844
But nothing is prepared yet.

178
00:09:32,928 --> 00:09:35,847
Unlike other products,
experience is key for Home-AI.

179
00:09:35,931 --> 00:09:38,225
We'll need to do a demonstration
to identify any issues.

180
00:09:38,308 --> 00:09:39,643
The schedule will be tight,

181
00:09:39,726 --> 00:09:41,978
so let's prepare for it
like it's our final check before launch.

182
00:09:43,021 --> 00:09:45,899
I guess that means
we'll be incredibly busy.

183
00:09:45,982 --> 00:09:49,569
Even so, presenting the project
within a month is pushing it.

184
00:09:50,153 --> 00:09:52,197
When does testing
for the living appliances finish?

185
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:55,784
Uh, everything except the washing machine
should be wrapping up soon. Yeah.

186
00:09:55,867 --> 00:09:57,869
Can we get the brochures
made within a month?

187
00:09:57,953 --> 00:10:00,747
Oh, brochures?
Yes, that's definitely doable.

188
00:10:00,831 --> 00:10:01,706
And kitchen appliances?

189
00:10:01,790 --> 00:10:04,501
Uh… I haven't even had a meeting
with them yet.

190
00:10:04,584 --> 00:10:05,794
We have a long way to go.

191
00:10:05,877 --> 00:10:07,879
Then all we need is for you to
pick up the pace, Ms. Cha.

192
00:10:09,256 --> 00:10:11,258
As long as everyone here
does their part,

193
00:10:11,341 --> 00:10:12,884
then I'll coordinate everything else.

194
00:10:12,968 --> 00:10:14,386
-Sure.
-Sure.

195
00:10:14,469 --> 00:10:16,263
As for you, Ms. Cha,

196
00:10:16,346 --> 00:10:18,723
please see me in the showroom
after we finish this meeting.

197
00:10:21,977 --> 00:10:22,978
Yes, sir.

198
00:10:24,729 --> 00:10:27,441
[coworkers chattering, laughing]

199
00:10:33,155 --> 00:10:34,489
A-A demo?

200
00:10:34,573 --> 00:10:35,574
Yes.

201
00:10:35,657 --> 00:10:38,201
Apparently,
they're inviting overseas buyers.

202
00:10:39,244 --> 00:10:41,788
If President Han
delivers real results with that,

203
00:10:41,872 --> 00:10:45,125
the Vice President
can forget about the next President spot.

204
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:47,461
And then our side
will be dead in the water.

205
00:10:47,544 --> 00:10:48,628
We can't let that…

206
00:10:48,712 --> 00:10:50,297
[tense music playing]

207
00:10:50,380 --> 00:10:51,590
We-We can't let that happen.

208
00:10:51,673 --> 00:10:53,675
How's the digging into that punk
coming along?

209
00:10:53,758 --> 00:10:55,218
Oh, uh, I haven't--

210
00:10:55,302 --> 00:10:56,887
Well, hurry up and find something.

211
00:10:58,096 --> 00:11:01,975
And also, figure out a way
to sabotage the demo while you're at it.

212
00:11:02,976 --> 00:11:05,145
Uh, b-but what if we sabotage the demo?

213
00:11:05,228 --> 00:11:06,688
Wouldn't that take a toll
on the company too?

214
00:11:06,771 --> 00:11:10,984
What? You think a massive company
like this will go under over one bad demo?

215
00:11:11,067 --> 00:11:14,946
Once it fails, we'll hold Han U-jin
and Kang Si-woo responsible,

216
00:11:15,030 --> 00:11:16,990
and take over the Home-AI project.

217
00:11:17,073 --> 00:11:18,158
Oh!

218
00:11:18,241 --> 00:11:21,036
And set up a meeting
with that guy we talked about, okay?

219
00:11:21,661 --> 00:11:22,662
Yes, sir.

220
00:11:25,624 --> 00:11:26,625
[sighs]

221
00:11:34,216 --> 00:11:35,342
What did you want to see me for?

222
00:11:35,425 --> 00:11:37,135
To give you more work, of course.

223
00:11:37,219 --> 00:11:39,554
You've already assigned me an
excessive amount of work.

224
00:11:40,096 --> 00:11:40,972
Is there more?

225
00:11:41,056 --> 00:11:42,516
You seem to have a lot of complaints.

226
00:11:42,599 --> 00:11:43,934
I can't say I don't.

227
00:11:45,060 --> 00:11:48,855
I just wanted to deliver
a high-quality product

228
00:11:48,939 --> 00:11:51,233
without having to race
against the clock this time.

229
00:11:51,316 --> 00:11:53,693
What's the biggest issue
with the kitchen side of things?

230
00:11:54,319 --> 00:11:55,529
The issue is Mr. Ko.

231
00:11:56,404 --> 00:11:58,865
I asked for help many times,
but he won't respond.

232
00:11:58,949 --> 00:12:00,992
Then I'll take care of that for you.

233
00:12:01,076 --> 00:12:02,369
How's that?

234
00:12:02,452 --> 00:12:04,246
By playing the President card.

235
00:12:04,329 --> 00:12:06,039
That's why we're reporting
to her directly.

236
00:12:06,122 --> 00:12:08,291
Wow. You wanted your work
to speak for itself.

237
00:12:08,375 --> 00:12:09,751
You play politics too, huh?

238
00:12:09,834 --> 00:12:12,837
Making things work isn't playing politics.
It's coordination.

239
00:12:12,921 --> 00:12:14,589
In that case,

240
00:12:14,673 --> 00:12:17,676
could I use the Mr. Kang card
sometimes too?

241
00:12:17,759 --> 00:12:19,177
That, I can't allow.

242
00:12:21,388 --> 00:12:22,639
Why not?

243
00:12:22,722 --> 00:12:25,308
I tend to find it hard to draw the
professional-personal line around you.

244
00:12:25,934 --> 00:12:26,810
[scoffs]

245
00:12:29,354 --> 00:12:31,064
Will you be working late again today?

246
00:12:31,147 --> 00:12:32,274
Probably.

247
00:12:32,857 --> 00:12:34,025
[Ji-yoon] Hmm.

248
00:12:34,109 --> 00:12:35,151
-[footsteps]
-[Jung-in pants]

249
00:12:35,235 --> 00:12:36,486
I just heard a rumor.

250
00:12:36,570 --> 00:12:38,572
-Oh, yeah? What rumor?
-Apparently, if you kiss in here,

251
00:12:38,655 --> 00:12:40,282
your married life will be smooth sailing.

252
00:12:40,365 --> 00:12:43,118
-[Jung-in] What are you talking about?
-Just give me one kiss.

253
00:12:43,201 --> 00:12:45,245
-No, we can't. People will see us!
-No one's coming now. Just one.

254
00:12:45,328 --> 00:12:46,496
[romantic music playing]

255
00:12:46,580 --> 00:12:47,747
[gasps softly]

256
00:12:49,124 --> 00:12:50,125
[gasps]

257
00:12:50,917 --> 00:12:53,086
[softly] Those two?
I never would've guessed it.

258
00:12:53,169 --> 00:12:55,171
-They'd say the same about us.
-[chuckles]

259
00:12:57,132 --> 00:12:58,091
Your foot.

260
00:12:59,175 --> 00:13:00,176
I'm sorry.

261
00:13:05,724 --> 00:13:07,309
I could get used to this too.

262
00:13:07,392 --> 00:13:10,061
As nice as this is,
we can't stay here forever.

263
00:13:10,145 --> 00:13:11,313
Then what?

264
00:13:12,188 --> 00:13:13,315
Take your time coming back.

265
00:13:19,613 --> 00:13:22,490
So, what do you think?
You think we have a…

266
00:13:26,161 --> 00:13:27,162
-Geez!
-[grunts]

267
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:29,748
[groans]

268
00:13:29,831 --> 00:13:31,666
Jung-in! No, I mean, Ms. Choi.

269
00:13:32,542 --> 00:13:33,585
[chuckles]

270
00:13:33,668 --> 00:13:35,837
Guess no one's coming here for a while.

271
00:13:37,881 --> 00:13:40,091
[in French] Excellent.
That's it for today.

272
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:43,219
See you next time. Thank you. Goodbye.

273
00:13:43,303 --> 00:13:45,388
[class] Thank you, goodbye.

274
00:13:49,643 --> 00:13:51,728
Everyone, come and pick up
your pop quizzes.

275
00:13:58,902 --> 00:14:00,904
Oh! How sweet!

276
00:14:00,987 --> 00:14:02,030
What's this?

277
00:14:02,113 --> 00:14:02,947
[Jae-in] "On y go."

278
00:14:03,907 --> 00:14:04,991
Where to?

279
00:14:05,075 --> 00:14:06,034
Somewhere fun.

280
00:14:06,534 --> 00:14:08,620
[gentle music playing]

281
00:14:09,913 --> 00:14:10,914
[groans, sighs]

282
00:14:13,416 --> 00:14:15,669
The other day
you told me you had many talents.

283
00:14:15,752 --> 00:14:18,004
-Is this one of them?
-No, I'm not good at this.

284
00:14:18,088 --> 00:14:20,340
That's why we're making a bet.

285
00:14:20,924 --> 00:14:21,925
What kind of bet?

286
00:14:22,008 --> 00:14:24,678
Well, if I win then
you go on a date with me.

287
00:14:24,761 --> 00:14:25,845
Are you asking me out?

288
00:14:25,929 --> 00:14:26,888
Does it sound like it?

289
00:14:28,306 --> 00:14:29,933
Then I guess I'm good at that too.

290
00:14:31,017 --> 00:14:31,893
And if I win, what?

291
00:14:31,976 --> 00:14:34,229
That won't happen,
so just tell me what you want.

292
00:14:34,312 --> 00:14:36,314
All right, let's do this then.

293
00:14:36,398 --> 00:14:37,399
Sweet!

294
00:14:41,152 --> 00:14:42,779
-[groans]
-[chuckles]

295
00:14:53,665 --> 00:14:54,582
[clears throat]

296
00:14:57,627 --> 00:14:59,546
All right, your turn.

297
00:15:00,171 --> 00:15:01,756
All right, fine.

298
00:15:07,554 --> 00:15:09,431
[intense music playing]

299
00:15:09,514 --> 00:15:10,348
Show me what you've got.

300
00:15:14,310 --> 00:15:16,187
[upbeat disco music playing]

301
00:15:17,605 --> 00:15:19,149
-Ooh.
-[huffs]

302
00:15:19,774 --> 00:15:21,693
-[chuckles]
-[sucks teeth]

303
00:15:21,776 --> 00:15:23,069
[grunts]

304
00:15:33,079 --> 00:15:34,080
[No-ah huffs]

305
00:15:36,750 --> 00:15:38,877
So, do I just tell you what I want now?

306
00:15:39,669 --> 00:15:40,503
Yeah.

307
00:15:41,087 --> 00:15:42,088
I want you to be my tutor.

308
00:15:42,839 --> 00:15:43,673
Huh?

309
00:15:43,757 --> 00:15:47,260
I can manage reading and writing,
but the pronunciation's too hard.

310
00:15:47,343 --> 00:15:48,386
Tutor me on the weekends.

311
00:15:49,012 --> 00:15:50,013
I don't come cheap, you know.

312
00:15:50,597 --> 00:15:51,765
I have a pretty high salary.

313
00:15:51,848 --> 00:15:54,768
-[chuckles]
-[chuckles]

314
00:15:54,851 --> 00:15:56,394
Okay, deal!

315
00:15:56,978 --> 00:15:57,854
Deal!

316
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:12,786
[amusing music playing]

317
00:16:19,876 --> 00:16:21,961
Since we're both busy this week.

318
00:16:27,175 --> 00:16:28,968
HOW TO SABOTAGE DEMO?

319
00:16:30,553 --> 00:16:32,764
[sighs]

320
00:16:33,389 --> 00:16:34,516
[phone buzzes]

321
00:16:34,599 --> 00:16:35,475
PRESIDENT HAN U-JIN

322
00:16:37,977 --> 00:16:38,812
Yes, ma'am.

323
00:16:38,895 --> 00:16:39,896
Yes.

324
00:16:41,397 --> 00:16:42,607
No, no, not at all.

325
00:16:43,107 --> 00:16:44,359
Yes, I understand.

326
00:16:44,442 --> 00:16:46,194
Yes. I will take care of it right away.

327
00:16:46,778 --> 00:16:49,239
Yes, yes. Yes. Thank you. Goodbye. yes.

328
00:16:53,326 --> 00:16:54,702
Damn it.

329
00:16:57,288 --> 00:16:58,289
Ms. Yoon No-ah.

330
00:16:59,749 --> 00:17:00,583
Sir?

331
00:17:01,084 --> 00:17:03,545
You may go and help with the task force.

332
00:17:04,128 --> 00:17:07,131
Keep it within reason so it doesn't
interfere with your main tasks.

333
00:17:07,215 --> 00:17:08,508
Do you understand?

334
00:17:08,591 --> 00:17:09,592
Yes.

335
00:17:09,676 --> 00:17:12,053
[tense music playing]

336
00:17:12,136 --> 00:17:13,137
[sighs]

337
00:17:22,230 --> 00:17:24,148
How dare he play the President card?

338
00:17:24,232 --> 00:17:26,317
What the… [breathing heavily]

339
00:17:30,905 --> 00:17:34,033
[muttering] Just who does he think he is?

340
00:17:34,117 --> 00:17:35,326
[phone buzzes]

341
00:17:40,456 --> 00:17:42,709
[Young-sam] Tell me,
why haven't you replied yet?

342
00:17:42,792 --> 00:17:44,878
Do you want that promotion or what?

343
00:17:46,713 --> 00:17:48,756
[smacks lips, inhales deeply]

344
00:17:50,425 --> 00:17:52,343
[smacks lips, groans]

345
00:17:53,595 --> 00:17:55,054
Damn.

346
00:17:56,472 --> 00:17:58,975
Are you okay? Did something happen?

347
00:17:59,058 --> 00:18:01,227
No, I'm just so far behind
on my loan payment.

348
00:18:01,311 --> 00:18:02,645
[gasps] Oh, no.

349
00:18:03,646 --> 00:18:05,481
[whispering] It's okay. It's okay.
You'll be fine.

350
00:18:08,443 --> 00:18:09,861
[Kee-tae, whispering] Snap out of it.

351
00:18:16,159 --> 00:18:19,412
The dishwasher, water dispenser,
and oven are taken care of.

352
00:18:19,495 --> 00:18:20,788
-And the most important…
-Yeah.

353
00:18:20,872 --> 00:18:22,040
…is the refrigerator.

354
00:18:22,123 --> 00:18:25,209
Besides it being the hub for Home-AI,
I'd like to add other features to it.

355
00:18:25,293 --> 00:18:26,252
Like what exactly?

356
00:18:26,336 --> 00:18:27,587
A "food manager."

357
00:18:28,338 --> 00:18:32,550
Basically, it tracks what ingredients
are in the fridge, lists them out,

358
00:18:32,634 --> 00:18:35,511
and it can even suggest recipes you
can make with whatever you have in there.

359
00:18:35,595 --> 00:18:36,888
Wow.

360
00:18:37,430 --> 00:18:39,766
You never run out of things
you want to do, do you?

361
00:18:39,849 --> 00:18:40,808
And you?

362
00:18:40,892 --> 00:18:43,102
Do you have any ideas
since working on kitchen appliances?

363
00:18:43,728 --> 00:18:45,146
There was but I gave up,

364
00:18:45,229 --> 00:18:47,148
because they said it was a no-go.

365
00:18:47,231 --> 00:18:48,149
What was it?

366
00:18:48,232 --> 00:18:51,486
My sister once forgot a pot
on the induction cooktop,

367
00:18:51,569 --> 00:18:53,237
and everything burned completely.

368
00:18:53,321 --> 00:18:55,949
So then, I thought it would be great if
we could somehow

369
00:18:56,032 --> 00:18:58,242
control the cooktop remotely.

370
00:18:58,326 --> 00:19:00,161
But it's not allowed
under safety standards.

371
00:19:00,244 --> 00:19:01,120
Hmm?

372
00:19:01,788 --> 00:19:05,124
It's meant for safety,
but it didn't meet safety standards?

373
00:19:05,667 --> 00:19:06,501
It doesn't make sense.

374
00:19:06,584 --> 00:19:08,920
There were remotely controlled products
on the market before.

375
00:19:09,462 --> 00:19:12,048
With the safety standards changing,
no one's allowed to develop it now.

376
00:19:12,131 --> 00:19:13,967
[Ji-yoon] Hmm.

377
00:19:14,050 --> 00:19:15,218
[gasps] No-ah,

378
00:19:15,802 --> 00:19:16,928
see if you can crack this.

379
00:19:17,679 --> 00:19:19,806
-What?
-Someone has to crack this

380
00:19:19,889 --> 00:19:21,057
once and for all.

381
00:19:21,140 --> 00:19:23,685
It’s basically a race
to see who lands on the moon first.

382
00:19:24,602 --> 00:19:28,439
So, you want me to be Neil Armstrong?

383
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:30,274
Mmm.

384
00:19:30,358 --> 00:19:32,485
[tender music playing]

385
00:19:36,114 --> 00:19:37,031
Mr. Kang!

386
00:19:37,699 --> 00:19:39,450
I haven't seen you all day.

387
00:19:39,951 --> 00:19:41,285
Yeah, I was in a meeting.

388
00:19:42,453 --> 00:19:43,371
Anyone see where Ms. Cha went?

389
00:19:43,454 --> 00:19:46,457
Oh, yeah. Ms. Cha's in a meeting as well.
Yeah.

390
00:19:46,541 --> 00:19:47,667
Oh, looks like she's done.

391
00:19:50,753 --> 00:19:51,963
[Ji-yoon] It's Mr. Kang.

392
00:19:55,967 --> 00:19:58,177
I just met with Planning Team 1.

393
00:19:58,261 --> 00:20:00,179
Okay. Good work, Ms. Cha.

394
00:20:08,604 --> 00:20:09,814
Did you have anything else to say?

395
00:20:10,773 --> 00:20:11,774
Ah.

396
00:20:12,275 --> 00:20:14,569
I think we can start discussing
the design now.

397
00:20:14,652 --> 00:20:16,487
Should I set up a meeting
with the Design Team?

398
00:20:16,571 --> 00:20:18,614
I'll take care of the design matters.

399
00:20:18,698 --> 00:20:21,367
You just focus on the tasks
you already have.

400
00:20:21,451 --> 00:20:23,453
Well, should I give the person in charge
a heads-up?

401
00:20:23,536 --> 00:20:24,620
No need.

402
00:20:24,704 --> 00:20:27,165
I will have a talk
with Ms. Choi Soo-jin myself.

403
00:20:30,209 --> 00:20:31,210
Sure.

404
00:20:38,593 --> 00:20:40,011
I'll go see the Development Team.

405
00:20:55,485 --> 00:20:57,904
[playful music playing]

406
00:20:58,863 --> 00:20:59,864
[chuckles]

407
00:21:14,045 --> 00:21:16,798
All right, so a map view
pops up like this.

408
00:21:17,799 --> 00:21:20,885
If you tap on the products
at each location,

409
00:21:20,968 --> 00:21:23,971
you can see their current status
and control them.

410
00:21:24,055 --> 00:21:26,933
Plus, it can identify family members
by voice

411
00:21:27,016 --> 00:21:28,559
to provide personalized management.

412
00:21:28,643 --> 00:21:29,602
Right.

413
00:21:29,685 --> 00:21:31,979
It has all the features it needs
to be the Home-AI Hub.

414
00:21:32,063 --> 00:21:34,774
That's right.
Uh, but regarding that food manager idea…

415
00:21:34,857 --> 00:21:35,983
Yes?

416
00:21:36,067 --> 00:21:37,068
Look.

417
00:21:38,611 --> 00:21:41,239
So you're saying you want to put a camera
in the fridge

418
00:21:41,322 --> 00:21:42,698
to manage the ingredients, right?

419
00:21:42,782 --> 00:21:43,783
Yes, that's what I want.

420
00:21:43,866 --> 00:21:45,243
But look at that.

421
00:21:45,326 --> 00:21:48,496
What about the items in the back, or
the things stacked on top of each other?

422
00:21:48,579 --> 00:21:50,623
Like I said, installing a camera
isn't going to work.

423
00:21:50,706 --> 00:21:54,544
The inside of a refrigerator
is as unreadable as the human mind.

424
00:21:54,627 --> 00:21:56,295
What should we do?

425
00:21:56,379 --> 00:21:58,214
Is there no other way to achieve it?

426
00:21:58,297 --> 00:21:59,465
Is there?

427
00:21:59,549 --> 00:22:00,842
There's not.

428
00:22:01,467 --> 00:22:03,427
But do we have to do this?

429
00:22:03,511 --> 00:22:06,347
We're already adding
plenty of other features as it is.

430
00:22:06,430 --> 00:22:08,432
Exactly. We can't do all of this
in a month.

431
00:22:08,516 --> 00:22:12,103
But the whole point of a refrigerator
is storing and managing food.

432
00:22:12,186 --> 00:22:14,230
I really want to pull this off
for this project.

433
00:22:14,313 --> 00:22:15,690
I'd like to do that too.

434
00:22:15,773 --> 00:22:18,568
We just don't have anyone
who has enough time for it.

435
00:22:18,651 --> 00:22:19,485
It'll have to wait.

436
00:22:19,569 --> 00:22:22,196
Then, what if I can find someone else?

437
00:22:22,280 --> 00:22:23,281
From where?

438
00:22:23,364 --> 00:22:25,074
Someone from the outside if I have to.

439
00:22:25,158 --> 00:22:26,742
Go and find someone then.

440
00:22:27,577 --> 00:22:29,245
Make sure you get a Gen AI expert.

441
00:22:29,328 --> 00:22:30,454
GEN AI: GENERATIVE AI

442
00:22:30,538 --> 00:22:31,455
Yes, sir.

443
00:22:35,835 --> 00:22:37,420
[no audible dialogue]

444
00:22:39,463 --> 00:22:42,800
[no audible dialogue]

445
00:22:42,884 --> 00:22:44,552
[somber music playing]

446
00:22:44,635 --> 00:22:45,636
[sighs]

447
00:22:46,596 --> 00:22:47,889
They're just coworkers.

448
00:22:48,764 --> 00:22:51,225
I can't be bothered
about stuff like that too.

449
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:08,910
Oh, Mr. Kang.

450
00:23:17,001 --> 00:23:18,753
You know,
I barely got to see your face today,

451
00:23:18,836 --> 00:23:20,296
and now you're leaving
without saying a word?

452
00:23:20,880 --> 00:23:22,256
You seemed busy, so…

453
00:23:23,341 --> 00:23:25,259
You seem completely fine, Ms. Ji-yoon.

454
00:23:25,343 --> 00:23:26,928
Because I've been struggling all day.

455
00:23:27,011 --> 00:23:27,845
Me too.

456
00:23:30,473 --> 00:23:33,351
[tender music playing]

457
00:23:35,728 --> 00:23:37,271
Looks like you'll go home alone today too.

458
00:23:39,482 --> 00:23:40,900
Do you have a lot of work left?

459
00:23:40,983 --> 00:23:42,568
Hmm. A little.

460
00:23:42,652 --> 00:23:43,694
[sighs]

461
00:23:43,778 --> 00:23:46,364
Seems like dating a workaholic
sure is hard.

462
00:23:46,447 --> 00:23:49,116
Then how about a date this weekend?

463
00:23:51,118 --> 00:23:51,953
Yes.

464
00:23:59,919 --> 00:24:01,963
-Congrats, man.
-Hey, let's drink!

465
00:24:02,046 --> 00:24:03,506
-Let's drink, come on.
-Cheers!

466
00:24:04,966 --> 00:24:07,385
[coworkers grunt]

467
00:24:07,969 --> 00:24:09,762
-Congrats on the promotion.
-Congrats.

468
00:24:09,845 --> 00:24:11,055
Thank you. [chuckles]

469
00:24:11,138 --> 00:24:14,934
Our resident associate Jeong-su
is finally making senior associate, huh?

470
00:24:15,017 --> 00:24:16,936
My team lead
really looked out for me this time.

471
00:24:17,019 --> 00:24:18,562
Didn't you guys go to the same college?

472
00:24:19,146 --> 00:24:21,315
Guess the school ties
worked out for you. [chuckles]

473
00:24:21,399 --> 00:24:24,193
It wasn't the school ties. It's thanks to
my dedication and hard work.

474
00:24:24,277 --> 00:24:27,530
You know, I hate the heat,
but I still went with him to the sauna.

475
00:24:27,613 --> 00:24:28,990
[chuckles]

476
00:24:29,073 --> 00:24:31,242
[coworker] That's my point.
If you two hadn't gone to the same school,

477
00:24:31,325 --> 00:24:33,202
do you think your team lead
would've taken you to the sauna?

478
00:24:33,286 --> 00:24:34,287
You're right about that.

479
00:24:34,370 --> 00:24:35,371
[chuckling]

480
00:24:35,454 --> 00:24:38,749
Hey, hey, hey, you got healthier
and promoted thanks to that, yeah?

481
00:24:41,502 --> 00:24:44,338
So, that just leaves you now, huh?

482
00:24:44,422 --> 00:24:47,258
Oh, is that it? [chuckles]
Geez. [clears throat]

483
00:24:47,341 --> 00:24:49,343
-Hey, it'll happen in no time, yeah?
-Yeah.

484
00:24:49,427 --> 00:24:50,553
-Hey. Let's drink.
-Yeah.

485
00:24:50,636 --> 00:24:51,846
[Jeong-su chuckles]

486
00:24:54,473 --> 00:24:56,392
Hey. So, did you guys hear about her?

487
00:24:56,475 --> 00:24:58,519
-The one who was on maternity leave…
-[phone buzzes]

488
00:24:58,602 --> 00:25:00,646
…and got promoted the second she returned.

489
00:25:00,730 --> 00:25:02,023
-Kim Mi-yeong?
-Mi-yeong, yeah.

490
00:25:02,106 --> 00:25:03,107
Yeah, she came back…

491
00:25:03,190 --> 00:25:04,775
[Han-gyeol] Dad, when are you coming home?

492
00:25:04,859 --> 00:25:08,070
Can you get me that bread with
the dinosaur stickers on your way back?

493
00:25:08,654 --> 00:25:11,198
Hey, uh, let me make a phone call
real quick.

494
00:25:11,282 --> 00:25:12,199
Oh, sure.

495
00:25:12,283 --> 00:25:13,409
So then what about Mi-yeong?

496
00:25:13,492 --> 00:25:15,202
I think she's got some connections.

497
00:25:17,580 --> 00:25:19,707
[Young-sam] Tell me,
why haven't you replied yet?

498
00:25:19,790 --> 00:25:21,417
Do you want that promotion or what?

499
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:23,586
[tense music playing]

500
00:25:30,801 --> 00:25:32,386
[Kee-tae] What is it
that you need me to do?

501
00:25:41,062 --> 00:25:44,148
[whimsical music playing]

502
00:25:44,982 --> 00:25:46,609
So, Mr. Kang.

503
00:25:46,692 --> 00:25:49,111
When did you start having feelings for me?

504
00:25:49,195 --> 00:25:50,154
Hmm.

505
00:25:50,821 --> 00:25:53,115
Maybe when you made me
play the bad guy

506
00:25:53,199 --> 00:25:55,117
while you took care of people
like the sun,

507
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:58,079
or when you asked if I was lonely.

508
00:25:59,538 --> 00:26:02,208
Or maybe it started long before that.

509
00:26:04,460 --> 00:26:05,461
You know, at some point,

510
00:26:05,544 --> 00:26:09,006
I caught myself looking at you
and smiling without even realizing it.

511
00:26:09,090 --> 00:26:12,676
Then, I can assume
all those compliments you gave me

512
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:14,762
were because you really liked me, right?

513
00:26:14,845 --> 00:26:16,722
Do I look like the type who would do that?

514
00:26:17,306 --> 00:26:18,516
Uh, no.

515
00:26:18,599 --> 00:26:20,059
And I'm actually glad you're not.

516
00:26:21,477 --> 00:26:23,479
You're brave and responsible,

517
00:26:23,562 --> 00:26:25,523
and you make everyone around feel at ease.

518
00:26:25,606 --> 00:26:28,067
-You're someone I want to learn from.
-I am?

519
00:26:28,150 --> 00:26:29,443
Except for the snacks.

520
00:26:29,527 --> 00:26:30,778
[chuckles]

521
00:26:30,861 --> 00:26:33,239
I had tteokbokki just last night.

522
00:26:36,283 --> 00:26:37,868
[gasps, breathing shakily]

523
00:26:42,248 --> 00:26:43,249
[sighs]

524
00:26:46,252 --> 00:26:47,169
Do you know him?

525
00:26:47,253 --> 00:26:48,421
Yes, that's my brother.

526
00:26:49,255 --> 00:26:52,425
What the heck is he doing out?
He should be studying for his SAT retake.

527
00:26:52,508 --> 00:26:53,592
Come on, come on.

528
00:26:53,676 --> 00:26:55,302
[yelps]

529
00:26:55,386 --> 00:26:57,805
[comical music playing]

530
00:27:03,769 --> 00:27:04,937
Playing hide-and seek a lot I see.

531
00:27:05,020 --> 00:27:06,605
[chuckles] I know, right?

532
00:27:24,874 --> 00:27:27,251
Okay, now. This is it. Let's get out.

533
00:27:32,673 --> 00:27:33,966
He looks so familiar.

534
00:27:36,051 --> 00:27:37,386
Where have I seen him before?

535
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:41,015
Why did he smile at me though?

536
00:27:50,399 --> 00:27:51,817
God, that was close.

537
00:27:53,027 --> 00:27:54,195
-[sighs]
-[sucks teeth]

538
00:27:54,278 --> 00:27:56,947
If he's taking the SAT,
he must be quite younger than you.

539
00:27:57,448 --> 00:27:58,616
12 years younger.

540
00:27:58,699 --> 00:27:59,867
He's the baby of the family.

541
00:28:02,328 --> 00:28:03,996
Is there anything you need to buy here?

542
00:28:06,916 --> 00:28:08,751
Well, can you help me pick out a toner?

543
00:28:08,834 --> 00:28:09,877
Sure.

544
00:28:11,795 --> 00:28:16,050
[Ga-eul, on radio] ♪ The important thing
Is where I'm standing ♪

545
00:28:17,176 --> 00:28:21,180
♪ It's a relief that by my side is… ♪

546
00:28:22,056 --> 00:28:24,850
[patron] Ga-eul is super popular now, huh?
This song's practically everywhere.

547
00:28:25,726 --> 00:28:28,521
Yeah, he blew up after B.A. posted
about him on social media.

548
00:28:30,898 --> 00:28:33,359
Ji-yoon, should we go somewhere else?

549
00:28:33,442 --> 00:28:34,568
I don't see anything I like here.

550
00:28:35,069 --> 00:28:36,362
Yes.

551
00:28:44,370 --> 00:28:46,997
We could've just gone to a café.
Why come all the way here?

552
00:28:47,081 --> 00:28:48,374
Language happens in real-life.

553
00:28:48,457 --> 00:28:49,708
Immersion is important.

554
00:28:51,877 --> 00:28:53,420
[quirky music playing]

555
00:29:08,185 --> 00:29:09,311
[chuckles]

556
00:29:14,692 --> 00:29:16,527
What's going on with you and Mr. Kang?

557
00:29:16,610 --> 00:29:18,487
And on the weekend, hold on…

558
00:29:18,571 --> 00:29:19,697
Why were you holding hands?

559
00:29:19,780 --> 00:29:21,115
Well…

560
00:29:21,198 --> 00:29:22,241
It just sort of happened.

561
00:29:22,324 --> 00:29:24,577
-So you two are dating?
-[gasps] Quiet.

562
00:29:25,995 --> 00:29:28,956
Wait a second, since when?
How did that happen?

563
00:29:29,039 --> 00:29:32,001
[sighs] Don't tell me.
At the baseball game?

564
00:29:32,084 --> 00:29:33,168
No, not then.

565
00:29:33,669 --> 00:29:35,671
We even trash-talked him
for being a jerk together.

566
00:29:35,754 --> 00:29:37,590
All that trash-talk

567
00:29:37,673 --> 00:29:39,133
somehow got me to understand him.

568
00:29:39,216 --> 00:29:41,135
Wow. Oh, geez.

569
00:29:42,177 --> 00:29:45,681
I mean, you must really like him
to be risking a relationship like this.

570
00:29:45,764 --> 00:29:47,808
Still, try to be more careful.

571
00:29:47,891 --> 00:29:50,185
Look at the chaos
the baseball game photo caused.

572
00:29:50,269 --> 00:29:51,895
Imagine what would happen
if word gets out.

573
00:29:51,979 --> 00:29:54,481
Exactly. So forget you ever saw us.

574
00:29:55,524 --> 00:29:56,775
[sighs]

575
00:30:00,195 --> 00:30:01,280
Why are they making a big deal?

576
00:30:01,947 --> 00:30:03,574
That's because I have a lot of flaws.

577
00:30:04,783 --> 00:30:05,826
And anyone

578
00:30:06,410 --> 00:30:07,745
can see that she's too good for me.

579
00:30:08,871 --> 00:30:10,164
And what are your flaws, sir?

580
00:30:13,167 --> 00:30:14,668
I like her more than she likes me.

581
00:30:15,586 --> 00:30:16,587
Ah.

582
00:30:18,255 --> 00:30:19,381
By the way,

583
00:30:20,007 --> 00:30:21,550
who's that kid you came with?

584
00:30:22,593 --> 00:30:24,428
'Cause he looks super young.

585
00:30:24,511 --> 00:30:26,680
He's the French TA.

586
00:30:26,764 --> 00:30:29,683
He's… [chuckles] …23 and in college.

587
00:30:29,767 --> 00:30:30,851
What? College?

588
00:30:32,353 --> 00:30:34,021
[sighs]

589
00:30:34,104 --> 00:30:36,940
You and I are both taking the hard path,
aren't we?

590
00:30:37,024 --> 00:30:39,360
-No. Not me.
-You're not?

591
00:30:39,943 --> 00:30:41,111
Well, not yet.

592
00:30:47,785 --> 00:30:49,870
Don't worry about No-ah, okay?

593
00:30:49,953 --> 00:30:51,580
She agreed to keep it secret.

594
00:30:52,373 --> 00:30:53,499
Okay.

595
00:30:54,875 --> 00:30:56,210
What should we have for dinner?

596
00:30:56,293 --> 00:30:59,296
Uh… let's find good places to eat nearby…

597
00:30:59,380 --> 00:31:00,214
Let's just head back.

598
00:31:01,590 --> 00:31:02,424
Sorry?

599
00:31:02,508 --> 00:31:04,176
My stomach's a little upset,

600
00:31:05,177 --> 00:31:06,345
so I don't really feel like eating out.

601
00:31:06,428 --> 00:31:07,513
Oh.

602
00:31:08,430 --> 00:31:11,850
Okay, then.
We can just have dinner separately.

603
00:31:11,934 --> 00:31:13,394
Let's eat at my place instead.

604
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:21,360
Did I put you on the spot
with the abrupt invite?

605
00:31:22,778 --> 00:31:24,947
[Ji-yoon] I've been waiting
for that actually.

606
00:31:25,030 --> 00:31:26,073
Well…

607
00:31:27,533 --> 00:31:28,367
a little.

608
00:31:30,285 --> 00:31:32,287
I may have rushed things a bit.

609
00:31:32,371 --> 00:31:34,373
[Ji-yoon] How adorably naive.

610
00:31:34,957 --> 00:31:36,250
-Maybe another time…
-Oh, no!

611
00:31:37,292 --> 00:31:38,377
It's not my first time there,

612
00:31:38,460 --> 00:31:41,672
and you're not feeling well,
so I guess I have no other choice then.

613
00:31:44,091 --> 00:31:47,469
Truth is, I'm making up an excuse
to be alone with you.

614
00:31:47,553 --> 00:31:48,637
What?

615
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:51,849
[laughing]

616
00:31:54,184 --> 00:31:57,730
[in French] I'd like to pay, please.

617
00:31:59,481 --> 00:32:01,191
Will that be by card?

618
00:32:01,859 --> 00:32:05,446
Yes.
In three installments, please.

619
00:32:06,113 --> 00:32:07,239
Pardon?

620
00:32:07,322 --> 00:32:08,782
Could you repeat that, please?

621
00:32:08,866 --> 00:32:11,160
Yes, in three installments!

622
00:32:11,243 --> 00:32:13,328
[in English] Can you speak English?

623
00:32:13,412 --> 00:32:14,913
Hey! Keep doing that, and you're fired.

624
00:32:14,997 --> 00:32:17,082
All right, all right. Repeat after me.

625
00:32:17,166 --> 00:32:19,543
[in French]
In three installments, please.

626
00:32:20,169 --> 00:32:21,253
[clicks tongue, inhales sharply]

627
00:32:21,336 --> 00:32:24,256
In three installments, please.

628
00:32:24,339 --> 00:32:26,341
The receipt, please.

629
00:32:26,425 --> 00:32:29,845
The receipt, please.

630
00:32:29,928 --> 00:32:32,389
Would you be my boyfriend?

631
00:32:33,307 --> 00:32:35,809
-Huh?
-[in English] Come on, repeat after me.

632
00:32:36,643 --> 00:32:40,439
[in French] Would you be my boyfriend?

633
00:32:41,899 --> 00:32:46,612
Would you be my boyfriend?

634
00:32:47,404 --> 00:32:49,782
Yes, I'd like that.

635
00:32:50,532 --> 00:32:52,201
[in English] What did you say "yes" to?

636
00:33:07,925 --> 00:33:11,303
I thought you said you were a good cook.

637
00:33:11,386 --> 00:33:13,847
I said I liked cooking,
I didn't say I was good at it.

638
00:33:13,931 --> 00:33:15,098
You're right.

639
00:33:15,849 --> 00:33:16,683
You said that.

640
00:33:18,060 --> 00:33:20,479
Okay so what you're making now is…

641
00:33:20,562 --> 00:33:22,773
I'll make you
a shrimp, tomato, and zucchini pasta.

642
00:33:22,856 --> 00:33:25,234
Sounds like there's gonna be a lot
of chopping to do.

643
00:33:25,317 --> 00:33:27,778
So you should just sit back
and relax while I cook.

644
00:33:27,861 --> 00:33:29,321
[chuckles]

645
00:33:29,404 --> 00:33:31,073
If I sit back and relax,

646
00:33:31,156 --> 00:33:32,658
we'll have this for breakfast.

647
00:33:33,992 --> 00:33:34,993
[sighs]

648
00:34:00,686 --> 00:34:02,813
Okay, so you can do things your own way.

649
00:34:02,896 --> 00:34:04,690
And I'll do things my way.

650
00:34:05,190 --> 00:34:07,067
-Sound good?
-Yes.

651
00:34:20,038 --> 00:34:22,916
So why were you going back
to the States, huh?

652
00:34:23,500 --> 00:34:25,252
Because at that time,
I had no reason to stay here.

653
00:34:26,169 --> 00:34:27,212
What about your family?

654
00:34:27,296 --> 00:34:30,757
I only see my father once a year
on mother's death anniversary.

655
00:34:31,466 --> 00:34:32,718
Even at his age,

656
00:34:33,218 --> 00:34:36,013
he still feels uncomfortable to be around.

657
00:34:36,847 --> 00:34:37,848
Oh.

658
00:34:38,432 --> 00:34:40,559
There was no one
I'd regret leaving here,

659
00:34:40,642 --> 00:34:43,228
and the States are easier
for Three-No-Man to work in.

660
00:34:43,937 --> 00:34:46,273
But then I stopped you from leaving.

661
00:34:46,356 --> 00:34:47,316
Yes.

662
00:34:48,567 --> 00:34:51,695
Ms. Ji-yoon, you're the only variable
that changes my plans.

663
00:34:53,780 --> 00:34:56,033
[somber classical music playing]

664
00:35:05,959 --> 00:35:07,252
I made…

665
00:35:08,587 --> 00:35:10,380
I made you hide all day today.

666
00:35:12,507 --> 00:35:13,467
I'm sorry.

667
00:35:13,550 --> 00:35:16,053
That's because of me, not because of you.

668
00:35:17,471 --> 00:35:19,389
I'm the reason that you had to hide,

669
00:35:19,890 --> 00:35:21,475
so why are you the one apologizing?

670
00:35:22,476 --> 00:35:23,352
Besides

671
00:35:23,435 --> 00:35:26,897
that word carries more weight
the more sparingly you say it.

672
00:35:28,106 --> 00:35:30,025
Please don't say that
when you're around me.

673
00:35:30,609 --> 00:35:31,610
Especially at work.

674
00:35:31,693 --> 00:35:33,695
That explains the "no sorry" part.

675
00:35:33,779 --> 00:35:34,905
You got me.

676
00:35:34,988 --> 00:35:36,156
[sighs]

677
00:35:37,157 --> 00:35:40,369
Looks like I've uncovered
all of the Three-No-Man's secrets.

678
00:35:40,452 --> 00:35:42,996
The moment you uncover
all of someone else's secrets…

679
00:35:44,247 --> 00:35:45,248
You get eliminated.

680
00:35:49,795 --> 00:35:51,630
Since you're too pretty to eliminate,

681
00:35:53,465 --> 00:35:54,549
so I'll just have to make you forget.

682
00:36:06,144 --> 00:36:08,146
[upbeat K-pop music playing]

683
00:36:08,814 --> 00:36:10,107
[Ji-yoon] The smell of toothpaste.

684
00:36:11,483 --> 00:36:12,943
You're such a sly fox, Mr. Kang.

685
00:36:43,890 --> 00:36:46,226
Hmm. Look at Korea and America.

686
00:36:46,309 --> 00:36:49,980
The main ingredients people use
are completely different in each country.

687
00:36:50,063 --> 00:36:53,275
Don't you think the refrigerator
should be able to recognize all of that?

688
00:36:53,358 --> 00:36:55,402
That would be amazing, right?

689
00:36:55,485 --> 00:36:56,862
[can pops]

690
00:36:56,945 --> 00:36:58,613
Are you drinking beer right now?

691
00:36:58,697 --> 00:37:01,241
Pu-erh tea for you, and beer for me.

692
00:37:01,324 --> 00:37:02,159
Cheers!

693
00:37:05,078 --> 00:37:06,621
Go to sleep.

694
00:37:06,705 --> 00:37:10,167
[yawns] I don't want to.
I'm not going to sleep.

695
00:37:11,293 --> 00:37:13,879
-Sleep.
-I'm telling you, I'm not sleepy at all.

696
00:37:32,981 --> 00:37:34,483
[Kee-tae] What is it
that you need me to do?

697
00:37:34,983 --> 00:37:37,861
[Young-sam] Dig into Kang Si-woo
and find his weakness.

698
00:37:40,906 --> 00:37:41,907
[Kee-tae] Mr. Kang!

699
00:37:45,952 --> 00:37:48,205
-Have you eaten already?
-Yes.

700
00:37:48,288 --> 00:37:49,456
It'd be nice to eat together,

701
00:37:49,539 --> 00:37:51,249
but you're so busy
that you're always eating alone.

702
00:37:51,333 --> 00:37:53,168
[chuckles] I don't really mind.

703
00:37:53,251 --> 00:37:55,253
[stammers] We're family now, aren't we?

704
00:37:55,337 --> 00:37:58,548
So part of being a family is sitting down
and sharing meals together…

705
00:37:58,632 --> 00:37:59,841
Would you like some tea?

706
00:37:59,925 --> 00:38:01,843
Why not? [chuckles]

707
00:38:02,636 --> 00:38:03,637
No need.

708
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:06,098
Allow me to bring a cup to you.
Please, take a seat.

709
00:38:06,181 --> 00:38:08,100
Oh, no.
I couldn't possibly do that. [chuckles]

710
00:38:10,310 --> 00:38:11,770
I will shamelessly take a seat, then.

711
00:38:23,782 --> 00:38:25,367
He won't let me get close to him.

712
00:38:25,867 --> 00:38:27,953
So how am I supposed to dig anything up?

713
00:38:32,916 --> 00:38:33,917
You're working hard.

714
00:38:35,127 --> 00:38:35,961
Mr. Kang.

715
00:38:41,883 --> 00:38:43,343
Looks like things aren't going so well.

716
00:38:43,426 --> 00:38:44,427
No.

717
00:38:45,262 --> 00:38:47,806
The Development Team
said it's going to be hard

718
00:38:47,889 --> 00:38:50,058
to develop the food manager
with their current workforce.

719
00:38:50,892 --> 00:38:53,937
So, I'm looking for a separate
Gen AI expert who can take it on.

720
00:38:54,479 --> 00:38:56,439
A Gen AI expert, hmm.

721
00:38:57,482 --> 00:39:00,527
Right, Lee Young-hun
would be perfect for it.

722
00:39:00,610 --> 00:39:02,863
Mr. Lee Young-hun,
who's currently on leave?

723
00:39:03,613 --> 00:39:04,865
Yes.

724
00:39:04,948 --> 00:39:07,284
Nobody else can match him in that field.

725
00:39:07,909 --> 00:39:09,828
He's returning soon,
so you should look into it.

726
00:39:09,911 --> 00:39:11,163
Great.

727
00:39:11,246 --> 00:39:12,747
Then I will reach out to him today.

728
00:39:17,752 --> 00:39:19,296
You do this whenever you can.

729
00:39:19,379 --> 00:39:21,173
Remind me who said we should be careful?

730
00:39:21,673 --> 00:39:23,550
Cut me some slack, will you?

731
00:39:24,176 --> 00:39:27,220
We've been so busy this week
we barely even saw each other.

732
00:39:28,305 --> 00:39:31,683
I mean, tell me, what kind of
secret meetings are you having

733
00:39:31,766 --> 00:39:34,019
that you're meeting with the President
day and night?

734
00:39:37,022 --> 00:39:38,440
That's confidential.

735
00:39:39,524 --> 00:39:40,525
No fair.

736
00:39:42,611 --> 00:39:45,197
Should we leave work together?

737
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:48,950
Yes! [gasps] Oh, I can't.

738
00:39:50,076 --> 00:39:51,077
Do you have plans?

739
00:39:51,161 --> 00:39:53,663
I have to practice a song today
for a friend's wedding.

740
00:39:53,747 --> 00:39:56,833
Hmm… Then I can drive you
to practice if you want.

741
00:39:58,043 --> 00:40:00,378
You don't have to, but if you insist.

742
00:40:01,171 --> 00:40:05,217
Since it's pitch-black outside
even when I clock out on the dot.

743
00:40:05,300 --> 00:40:07,344
So dangerous. [chuckles]

744
00:40:08,511 --> 00:40:10,472
-[Kee-tae] Mr. Kang.
-[gasps]

745
00:40:11,640 --> 00:40:12,474
Goodness.

746
00:40:14,601 --> 00:40:15,852
[footsteps approaching]

747
00:40:15,936 --> 00:40:18,313
-Gosh, you spilled it?
-Yeah.

748
00:40:18,396 --> 00:40:19,689
Are you all right?

749
00:40:19,773 --> 00:40:20,899
Yes, sir.

750
00:40:20,982 --> 00:40:22,776
Geez, you should've been more careful.

751
00:40:22,859 --> 00:40:23,902
I'll do it.

752
00:40:25,737 --> 00:40:26,988
What's the matter, huh?

753
00:40:27,072 --> 00:40:30,450
You took so long, I thought you were
picking the green tea leaves yourself.

754
00:40:32,410 --> 00:40:33,954
It's not green tea,

755
00:40:34,037 --> 00:40:35,538
it's hibiscus.

756
00:40:36,831 --> 00:40:37,874
Hibiscus.

757
00:40:43,004 --> 00:40:43,838
Blood?

758
00:40:43,922 --> 00:40:45,131
Well then, enjoy your tea.

759
00:40:45,215 --> 00:40:47,050
Wait, I thought we were drinking to…

760
00:40:51,054 --> 00:40:54,474
[sighs] Man, it's not easy
to get close to Mr. Kang.

761
00:40:56,393 --> 00:40:57,394
-[chuckles]
-[slurps]

762
00:40:57,936 --> 00:40:59,354
[groans] That's sour.

763
00:41:02,774 --> 00:41:04,276
So what do you do here exactly?

764
00:41:04,859 --> 00:41:06,236
Audio mixing.

765
00:41:06,319 --> 00:41:09,072
Can you show me?
I want to see how it's done.

766
00:41:15,495 --> 00:41:18,832
[acoustic pop music playing]

767
00:41:38,143 --> 00:41:39,936
[gasps]

768
00:41:43,398 --> 00:41:44,399
[music stops]

769
00:41:44,983 --> 00:41:48,987
I blend all these separate tracks together
to turn them into one cohesive song.

770
00:41:49,070 --> 00:41:50,238
Oh…

771
00:41:50,864 --> 00:41:52,949
It's kind of like my company.

772
00:41:53,033 --> 00:41:56,119
We also have different teams
collaborating to make one product.

773
00:41:56,703 --> 00:41:59,205
I never would've guessed that
you work at an electronics company.

774
00:41:59,289 --> 00:42:01,166
Why? I suddenly look grown-up?

775
00:42:01,249 --> 00:42:02,250
Mm-hmm.

776
00:42:02,334 --> 00:42:03,835
You must've worked really hard
in your life.

777
00:42:03,918 --> 00:42:06,755
Yeah, I kept my head down
and worked diligently.

778
00:42:07,255 --> 00:42:09,799
And what's the result?
You've seen how that turned out.

779
00:42:09,883 --> 00:42:11,217
Isn't it for the best though?

780
00:42:12,385 --> 00:42:14,179
You're better off
not marrying a jerk like that.

781
00:42:14,262 --> 00:42:16,765
That's true. I guess I got really lucky.

782
00:42:16,848 --> 00:42:17,849
Of course.

783
00:42:18,391 --> 00:42:19,893
And you got a young handsome guy now.

784
00:42:19,976 --> 00:42:21,478
[laughs]

785
00:42:22,437 --> 00:42:24,522
So, teacher, when are you teaching?

786
00:42:24,606 --> 00:42:25,648
Yeah, I should.

787
00:42:26,149 --> 00:42:29,152
Oh, next time, should we do it
at my place instead?

788
00:42:30,153 --> 00:42:31,654
It's closer to your place too.

789
00:42:32,697 --> 00:42:34,908
Hey… [scoffs] …um, come on.

790
00:42:35,867 --> 00:42:38,870
You can't just invite me
over to your place like that.

791
00:42:38,953 --> 00:42:40,038
Is that a bit too much?

792
00:42:46,586 --> 00:42:47,921
Then, what if we started dating?

793
00:42:48,004 --> 00:42:49,631
Why do you keep…

794
00:42:50,215 --> 00:42:51,132
Or wait.

795
00:42:52,634 --> 00:42:54,052
Are we actually already dating?

796
00:43:01,643 --> 00:43:02,560
[door opens]

797
00:43:02,644 --> 00:43:03,978
Lee Jae-in!

798
00:43:07,357 --> 00:43:08,316
What's this?

799
00:43:11,486 --> 00:43:13,405
You broke up with me
because you got a new girl?

800
00:43:13,488 --> 00:43:15,407
No. I'm not the cheating type of guy.

801
00:43:17,659 --> 00:43:18,493
Who are you?

802
00:43:18,576 --> 00:43:20,578
What's going on between you two, huh?

803
00:43:33,716 --> 00:43:34,884
You two talk.

804
00:43:34,968 --> 00:43:36,344
I'm going to leave now.

805
00:43:37,595 --> 00:43:38,805
-No-ah.
-Hey!

806
00:43:40,181 --> 00:43:41,057
Jae-in.

807
00:43:43,017 --> 00:43:44,269
Where are you going?

808
00:43:46,980 --> 00:43:47,981
[Jae-in] No-ah.

809
00:43:53,361 --> 00:43:54,195
No-ah.

810
00:43:54,279 --> 00:43:55,780
Call me Ms. Yoon.

811
00:43:56,573 --> 00:43:57,407
Okay. Ms. No-ah.

812
00:43:57,490 --> 00:43:59,284
[scoffs] Never mind.

813
00:44:00,285 --> 00:44:02,412
It doesn't matter
what you call me now, does it?

814
00:44:03,955 --> 00:44:04,956
You're fired now.

815
00:44:12,505 --> 00:44:13,506
Are you angry at me?

816
00:44:15,258 --> 00:44:16,926
When did you break up
with your girlfriend?

817
00:44:17,510 --> 00:44:20,013
Two months ago.
About the same time you did.

818
00:44:20,096 --> 00:44:21,139
Hmm.

819
00:44:22,891 --> 00:44:24,684
And you were totally fine with it?

820
00:44:24,767 --> 00:44:25,768
Yeah.

821
00:44:26,519 --> 00:44:27,854
I wasn't that sad actually.

822
00:44:29,731 --> 00:44:31,441
The feelings weren't there anymore.

823
00:44:34,110 --> 00:44:35,320
It's over, No-ah.

824
00:44:35,403 --> 00:44:37,280
My feelings for you are gone.

825
00:44:38,031 --> 00:44:40,158
Do you have any idea
how selfish you sound?

826
00:44:42,243 --> 00:44:43,912
What keeps a relationship going

827
00:44:44,996 --> 00:44:47,499
isn't that first spark you felt,
it's effort.

828
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:51,878
Have you even thought about how
she must've felt coming all this way here?

829
00:44:51,961 --> 00:44:53,796
How can effort ever turn into love?

830
00:44:56,716 --> 00:44:57,926
I don't think that's love.

831
00:45:06,518 --> 00:45:07,769
You're way too shallow.

832
00:45:09,270 --> 00:45:10,855
And I just hate that.

833
00:45:17,779 --> 00:45:18,780
That's not true.

834
00:45:19,781 --> 00:45:20,990
And I'm not shallow.

835
00:45:25,787 --> 00:45:27,080
[sighs]

836
00:45:43,471 --> 00:45:44,973
Thank you so much for the ride.

837
00:45:48,560 --> 00:45:49,394
I'll call you tonight.

838
00:46:12,792 --> 00:46:13,876
Hi.

839
00:46:16,921 --> 00:46:17,922
What's wrong?

840
00:46:19,507 --> 00:46:20,675
[Ga-eul] Long time no see.

841
00:46:23,595 --> 00:46:24,929
Have you been well?

842
00:46:25,013 --> 00:46:26,139
What's going on?

843
00:46:26,222 --> 00:46:28,266
Well, Ha-eun had to drop out last minute,

844
00:46:28,975 --> 00:46:30,310
so I told Seung-jun, and…

845
00:46:30,393 --> 00:46:33,229
Yeah, so Ga-eul insisted
he wanted to do it.

846
00:46:33,813 --> 00:46:35,773
How could you consider
doing a wedding song without me?

847
00:46:36,274 --> 00:46:37,358
It's Hye-ji's wedding.

848
00:46:38,526 --> 00:46:39,986
I was really hurt, you know.

849
00:46:41,946 --> 00:46:44,365
Hey, Ga-eul.
You should… [whispers] …get lost.

850
00:46:44,449 --> 00:46:47,201
-[chuckles] Mmm.
-[sighs] Let's practice.

851
00:46:48,786 --> 00:46:50,663
[Seung-jun]
Okay. Since it's the first day,

852
00:46:50,747 --> 00:46:53,583
let's just do a quick run-through
and call it a night. Yeah.

853
00:46:54,083 --> 00:46:55,376
Yeah. Sounds… Sounds good.

854
00:47:04,135 --> 00:47:05,136
[Hye-ji exclaims]

855
00:47:06,888 --> 00:47:09,057
-Hey. I'm going to go--
-[Seung-jun] Hey,

856
00:47:09,724 --> 00:47:11,017
Ga-eul got a car with his signing bonus.

857
00:47:11,851 --> 00:47:12,685
[Hye-ji] What?

858
00:47:12,769 --> 00:47:14,103
-This is yours?
-[Ga-eul] Yes.

859
00:47:14,187 --> 00:47:15,271
[Hye-ji gasps]

860
00:47:15,355 --> 00:47:17,106
Hop in, guys. I'll drop you all off.

861
00:47:17,190 --> 00:47:18,191
Whoa. No way.

862
00:47:18,858 --> 00:47:20,526
Let's go and stomp all over
his brand-new seats.

863
00:47:21,069 --> 00:47:22,737
-[gasps]
-[Seung-jun] Let's go, let's go! Come on.

864
00:47:24,697 --> 00:47:26,532
Whoa, nice car.

865
00:47:28,034 --> 00:47:31,329
Hey, remember when Seung-jun
drove his dad's car

866
00:47:31,412 --> 00:47:33,164
and we all went to Gangneung?

867
00:47:33,247 --> 00:47:36,125
[groans] Don't.
Just thinking about that day…

868
00:47:36,709 --> 00:47:38,211
We ran out of gas,
couldn't find a station,

869
00:47:38,294 --> 00:47:39,754
and called roadside assistance.

870
00:47:39,837 --> 00:47:43,633
Yeah. It was bad enough that we
were waiting in that boiling hot weather,

871
00:47:43,716 --> 00:47:45,677
but then Ga-eul started singing
in the middle of the road. [scoffs]

872
00:47:45,760 --> 00:47:46,844
[laughs] You're right.

873
00:47:46,928 --> 00:47:49,347
Yeah, someone even tossed him coins,
remember?

874
00:47:49,430 --> 00:47:50,682
That's right!

875
00:47:50,765 --> 00:47:52,183
[Hye-ji] Wow. He's come a long way.

876
00:48:01,317 --> 00:48:03,528
Well, I have my own place again.

877
00:48:06,280 --> 00:48:07,573
I'm happy for you.

878
00:48:08,241 --> 00:48:11,911
It's far away,
but you can still see the Hangang River.

879
00:48:12,870 --> 00:48:14,080
And there's a park in front.

880
00:48:15,623 --> 00:48:18,084
A family of cats live there too.

881
00:48:20,795 --> 00:48:24,090
I feel like the future
we imagined together

882
00:48:24,757 --> 00:48:25,758
has gotten closer.

883
00:48:28,261 --> 00:48:29,971
[Ji-yoon] Your once blurry dream

884
00:48:30,596 --> 00:48:32,432
is starting to come into focus.

885
00:48:33,808 --> 00:48:35,226
Congratulations, Ga-eul.

886
00:48:37,186 --> 00:48:40,356
Next time,
I'll invite you over with the others.

887
00:48:41,232 --> 00:48:42,483
You can drop me off over there.

888
00:48:43,359 --> 00:48:45,278
Why? Let me just drive you home.

889
00:48:46,404 --> 00:48:47,405
No.

890
00:48:48,281 --> 00:48:49,532
I don't think this is a good idea.

891
00:48:51,033 --> 00:48:53,870
Can't we at least stay friends?

892
00:48:55,121 --> 00:48:56,706
We were friends for so long

893
00:48:57,331 --> 00:48:58,666
before we even started dating.

894
00:49:01,127 --> 00:49:02,545
I don't think I can do that,

895
00:49:03,796 --> 00:49:04,881
not with you.

896
00:49:09,552 --> 00:49:10,678
Drop me off here.

897
00:49:43,711 --> 00:49:45,296
[phone buzzing]

898
00:49:49,759 --> 00:49:53,054
[buzzing continues]

899
00:49:57,558 --> 00:50:00,937
[sighs] If I answer now,
I might end up lying.

900
00:50:01,521 --> 00:50:04,148
MANAGER KANG SI-WOO

901
00:50:04,232 --> 00:50:05,608
Maybe later.

902
00:50:06,734 --> 00:50:08,069
I can tell him tomorrow.

903
00:50:11,447 --> 00:50:12,448
[sighs]

904
00:50:12,532 --> 00:50:14,826
[operator] Your call cannot be completed.
You will be connected…

905
00:50:14,909 --> 00:50:15,910
[line clicks]

906
00:50:20,414 --> 00:50:23,084
[Si-woo] After I wrap up my day,
I wait to hear from you.

907
00:50:24,335 --> 00:50:26,504
It's become my favorite part
of the day lately.

908
00:50:28,381 --> 00:50:31,384
But it looks like that little joy of mine

909
00:50:32,051 --> 00:50:33,052
is missing tonight.

910
00:50:54,115 --> 00:50:56,826
I just hope everything is okay with you.

911
00:50:58,995 --> 00:50:59,996
Sleep well.

912
00:51:17,680 --> 00:51:18,681
Did you sleep well?

913
00:51:19,265 --> 00:51:20,266
Yes.

914
00:51:21,309 --> 00:51:23,895
I hadn't played the drums in a long time,
so I was exhausted.

915
00:51:26,272 --> 00:51:27,940
-Yesterday, I…
-[Na-ri] Mr. Kang.

916
00:51:29,108 --> 00:51:30,568
Should we prepare some drinks too?

917
00:51:30,651 --> 00:51:32,028
Yes, please do.

918
00:51:32,111 --> 00:51:34,447
Oh, and, Ms. Cha,
could you please give me a hand?

919
00:51:35,406 --> 00:51:36,240
Hmm.

920
00:51:45,374 --> 00:51:47,627
[Soo-jin] This is the mock-up design
based on the new Home-AI concept

921
00:51:47,710 --> 00:51:49,295
proposed by the task force.

922
00:51:49,378 --> 00:51:50,838
We've hidden the voice recognition module

923
00:51:50,922 --> 00:51:53,007
and open-door sensors
for a clean aesthetic.

924
00:51:53,090 --> 00:51:56,677
Additionally, the camera is positioned
at the top center of the unit,

925
00:51:56,761 --> 00:51:59,805
while the screen remains
on the upper-right door panel.

926
00:51:59,889 --> 00:52:01,474
Well, it looks very nice and clean.

927
00:52:02,308 --> 00:52:04,685
The exterior design
hasn't changed much from before.

928
00:52:04,769 --> 00:52:08,940
Yes. Our assessment for now is that the
current placement and size of the screen

929
00:52:09,023 --> 00:52:10,024
is still our best option.

930
00:52:11,943 --> 00:52:13,194
Hmm.

931
00:52:14,028 --> 00:52:15,488
Should we proceed with this then?

932
00:52:16,322 --> 00:52:18,366
If we keep the current screen size,

933
00:52:18,449 --> 00:52:20,368
it will be released
as an ultra-premium model, right?

934
00:52:20,451 --> 00:52:21,827
Yes, it most likely will.

935
00:52:21,911 --> 00:52:24,413
Then how about we scale back
the screen size

936
00:52:24,497 --> 00:52:26,040
to lower the retail price?

937
00:52:28,751 --> 00:52:30,169
[Soo-jin] Hmm…

938
00:52:31,712 --> 00:52:35,091
If the screen is too small, it will look
like a purely functional gadget.

939
00:52:35,174 --> 00:52:39,929
I want this product to bring the Home-AI
experience to more and more people.

940
00:52:40,012 --> 00:52:42,098
That's why I'd like to
lower the retail price.

941
00:52:42,181 --> 00:52:44,558
Even if it means reducing the screen size.

942
00:52:44,642 --> 00:52:49,438
Consumers these days care prioritize
design elements over functional features.

943
00:52:49,522 --> 00:52:52,400
They want their fridge to look
like furniture, not a home appliance.

944
00:52:52,483 --> 00:52:55,528
Well, I think promoting Home-AI
should take priority.

945
00:52:57,405 --> 00:52:58,698
We call it aesthetics, right?

946
00:52:59,949 --> 00:53:02,576
We might just be
making electronic appliances,

947
00:53:02,660 --> 00:53:04,578
but it's still a value
we must never sacrifice.

948
00:53:05,788 --> 00:53:06,956
Yes, however--

949
00:53:07,039 --> 00:53:08,624
Let's move on to the final mock-up.

950
00:53:10,084 --> 00:53:11,419
Fine.

951
00:53:23,097 --> 00:53:26,767
As the product planner,
I wanted to explain my intent a bit more.

952
00:53:27,351 --> 00:53:29,228
I thought your point came across
clearly enough.

953
00:53:29,937 --> 00:53:30,896
I don't.

954
00:53:30,980 --> 00:53:33,941
I didn't get to explain everything
because you cut me off.

955
00:53:34,025 --> 00:53:36,736
Dragging out the discussion
could lead to needless conflict.

956
00:53:37,611 --> 00:53:40,114
When the mock-up is done,
we'll discuss this again.

957
00:53:47,955 --> 00:53:49,248
[sighs]

958
00:53:52,293 --> 00:53:53,544
How could he just

959
00:53:54,462 --> 00:53:56,756
cut me off like that
without even letting me finish?

960
00:53:56,839 --> 00:53:59,216
And he only listened to Ms. Choi.

961
00:54:01,510 --> 00:54:03,054
[sighs] This is ridiculous.

962
00:54:04,555 --> 00:54:06,682
Things like this
happen all the time at work.

963
00:54:08,392 --> 00:54:11,228
I know it's nothing,
so why am I feeling so miserable?

964
00:54:11,896 --> 00:54:12,897
[sighs]

965
00:54:14,065 --> 00:54:15,066
[exhales heavily]

966
00:54:28,621 --> 00:54:29,455
Oh, Ms. Choi.

967
00:54:29,538 --> 00:54:31,415
Where's Mr. Kang Si-woo?
Did he go somewhere?

968
00:54:31,499 --> 00:54:34,543
Oh, well, he's probably in a meeting
with the President.

969
00:54:35,169 --> 00:54:36,170
Did something happen?

970
00:54:36,253 --> 00:54:39,340
He just wasn't answering my calls.
I wonder when he's back.

971
00:54:39,423 --> 00:54:42,593
I'm not sure. He's been working late
every day, so…

972
00:54:42,676 --> 00:54:44,678
-[sighs]
-[phone buzzing]

973
00:54:44,762 --> 00:54:45,930
MANAGER KANG SI-WOO

974
00:54:47,264 --> 00:54:49,767
All right, then.
I'll reach out to him later.

975
00:54:49,850 --> 00:54:50,726
Okay.

976
00:54:50,810 --> 00:54:51,811
Oh…

977
00:54:53,395 --> 00:54:54,438
You did great today.

978
00:54:55,189 --> 00:54:57,733
Seeing you speak your mind
so confidently was impressive.

979
00:54:58,734 --> 00:55:01,320
Thanks to you,
I noticed what I've been missing too.

980
00:55:02,947 --> 00:55:04,240
I'll keep it in mind.

981
00:55:11,372 --> 00:55:12,748
-[sighs]
-[phone buzzes]

982
00:55:17,044 --> 00:55:19,004
[Si-woo] It's been hard to catch you
on the phone lately.

983
00:55:21,924 --> 00:55:24,385
You are so pathetic,

984
00:55:25,469 --> 00:55:26,512
Cha Ji-yoon.

985
00:55:28,848 --> 00:55:30,057
[secretary] Mr. Kang Si-woo?

986
00:55:31,350 --> 00:55:33,269
-Yes.
-She's ready for you.

987
00:55:33,352 --> 00:55:34,186
Thank you.

988
00:55:41,777 --> 00:55:43,112
[Young-hun] Ms. Cha Ji-yoon?

989
00:55:44,446 --> 00:55:45,447
Oh…

990
00:55:46,490 --> 00:55:48,242
Mr. Lee Young-hun?

991
00:55:48,868 --> 00:55:49,702
Yes.

992
00:55:49,785 --> 00:55:50,828
Nice to meet you.

993
00:55:50,911 --> 00:55:51,787
Nice to meet you too.

994
00:55:51,871 --> 00:55:53,038
Please sit down.

995
00:55:53,122 --> 00:55:54,123
-Sure.
-Yes.

996
00:55:56,458 --> 00:55:59,712
[chuckles] So we finally meet in person.

997
00:55:59,795 --> 00:56:00,629
I know, right.

998
00:56:00,713 --> 00:56:05,342
The post you wrote really helped clear up
the misunderstandings about Mr. Kang.

999
00:56:05,426 --> 00:56:06,719
[chuckles] Thank you.

1000
00:56:06,802 --> 00:56:09,555
Ah. So you need Gen AI technology?

1001
00:56:09,638 --> 00:56:10,472
Ah, yes.

1002
00:56:11,056 --> 00:56:14,560
Uh, we'd like an ingredient
recognition feature on the refrigerator.

1003
00:56:15,144 --> 00:56:17,521
Do you happen to have a project proposal?

1004
00:56:17,605 --> 00:56:19,190
-Uh, just a moment.
-Sure.

1005
00:56:24,612 --> 00:56:25,738
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

1006
00:56:29,116 --> 00:56:31,869
INGREDIENT RECOGNITION
AND RECIPE GENERATION

1007
00:56:33,245 --> 00:56:34,246
Hmm.

1008
00:56:38,000 --> 00:56:40,169
This looks fun. [chuckles]

1009
00:56:41,212 --> 00:56:42,880
If you're able to return to work,

1010
00:56:42,963 --> 00:56:45,549
I wanted to ask you
to start working on it right away.

1011
00:56:46,133 --> 00:56:48,886
Before another team snatches you up,
you know.

1012
00:56:48,969 --> 00:56:50,262
[chuckles]

1013
00:56:51,513 --> 00:56:52,681
Um…

1014
00:56:55,851 --> 00:56:57,978
That sounds good. I will give it a shot.

1015
00:56:59,271 --> 00:57:02,233
Uh, well, In that case,

1016
00:57:02,316 --> 00:57:06,487
would it be possible
to move up your return date a little?

1017
00:57:06,570 --> 00:57:08,405
Thing is,
we're on a really tight schedule.

1018
00:57:08,489 --> 00:57:09,323
Sure.

1019
00:57:09,406 --> 00:57:12,660
I've actually been itching to
get back to work anyway, so this is great.

1020
00:57:12,743 --> 00:57:13,744
I'll return right away.

1021
00:57:13,827 --> 00:57:15,621
[sighs] Thank you so much.

1022
00:57:16,247 --> 00:57:17,790
I look forward to working with you.

1023
00:57:17,873 --> 00:57:19,375
I look forward to working with you too.

1024
00:57:21,669 --> 00:57:23,045
-Well, take care then.
-You too.

1025
00:57:23,128 --> 00:57:24,630
-Thank you.
-Likewise.

1026
00:57:30,386 --> 00:57:32,513
CALLS
MISSED - MANAGER KANG SI-WOO

1027
00:58:01,458 --> 00:58:02,459
[phone buzzes]

1028
00:58:05,421 --> 00:58:07,464
MESSAGE FROM
SR. ASSOCIATE CHA JI-YOON

1029
00:58:09,133 --> 00:58:11,927
[Ji-yoon] Mr. Lee Young-hun
has agreed to join the task force.

1030
00:58:15,306 --> 00:58:16,557
[sighs]

1031
00:58:26,442 --> 00:58:27,943
[line ringing]

1032
00:58:29,987 --> 00:58:31,405
Yes, Mr. Noh.

1033
00:58:31,488 --> 00:58:32,948
I have agreed to join the task force.

1034
00:59:07,524 --> 00:59:09,193
You know, I missed you all day long.

1035
00:59:11,278 --> 00:59:12,863
You saw me during the day though.

1036
00:59:12,946 --> 00:59:14,239
I meant outside of work.

1037
00:59:28,879 --> 00:59:30,798
We've been missing each other
a lot lately.

1038
00:59:31,632 --> 00:59:33,675
That's because you're always so busy.

1039
00:59:35,344 --> 00:59:37,388
Were you very upset about earlier?

1040
00:59:37,471 --> 00:59:38,389
A little.

1041
00:59:41,183 --> 00:59:43,018
Well, no, very.

1042
00:59:43,102 --> 00:59:46,230
From now on, I'll put
all personal feelings aside at work.

1043
00:59:46,313 --> 00:59:48,065
and treat you strictly as a team member.

1044
00:59:48,857 --> 00:59:51,527
I might even be tougher on you.

1045
00:59:51,610 --> 00:59:53,654
My mind seems to understand it,

1046
00:59:54,488 --> 00:59:55,656
but my heart doesn't.

1047
00:59:56,365 --> 00:59:59,118
I want to keep it a secret,
but I hate that it is.

1048
00:59:59,827 --> 01:00:02,830
You seem so relaxed,
while I'm the only one feeling anxious.

1049
01:00:03,705 --> 01:00:06,250
And things that never really
bothered me before

1050
01:00:06,333 --> 01:00:09,002
just keep making me feel upset now.

1051
01:00:19,930 --> 01:00:23,100
These days, I can't focus on work.

1052
01:00:23,809 --> 01:00:25,769
Working out isn't so fun,

1053
01:00:25,853 --> 01:00:27,438
and I keep forgetting
to take my supplements.

1054
01:00:28,897 --> 01:00:31,066
And if I don't get to speak to you
before bed,

1055
01:00:31,150 --> 01:00:32,776
it feels like my whole day's ruined.

1056
01:00:34,611 --> 01:00:35,779
Like a teenager.

1057
01:00:35,863 --> 01:00:38,615
[chuckles] You do know how to coddle.

1058
01:00:39,491 --> 01:00:40,576
[groans]

1059
01:00:41,201 --> 01:00:42,619
I should whine more often.

1060
01:00:44,496 --> 01:00:45,330
As much as you want.

1061
01:00:46,165 --> 01:00:47,958
-Are you working tomorrow?
-Hmm.

1062
01:00:48,041 --> 01:00:51,003
I threw a little tantrum at the CEO
to have the day off tomorrow.

1063
01:00:52,171 --> 01:00:53,755
You really have become a teenager.

1064
01:00:54,756 --> 01:00:58,093
So, you wanna come over
for some late-night snacks?

1065
01:01:00,846 --> 01:01:02,890
There they are, the brows of truth.

1066
01:01:04,016 --> 01:01:05,934
[laughing]

1067
01:01:18,280 --> 01:01:20,616
Mr. Kang, do you feel uncomfortable
now that you're here?

1068
01:01:21,200 --> 01:01:22,784
Not at all. I'm comfortable.

1069
01:01:22,868 --> 01:01:24,703
I promise that I won't bite.

1070
01:01:25,370 --> 01:01:27,789
Just relax and feel at home.

1071
01:01:28,540 --> 01:01:29,541
How disappointing.

1072
01:01:29,625 --> 01:01:30,876
[chuckles]

1073
01:01:31,376 --> 01:01:32,544
Just a moment.

1074
01:01:42,721 --> 01:01:44,056
[phone buzzes]

1075
01:01:46,642 --> 01:01:48,310
[Ga-eul] Let's just keep things
comfortable between us

1076
01:01:48,393 --> 01:01:50,062
at least until we're done
with the wedding song.

1077
01:01:50,145 --> 01:01:51,605
I'll see you at practice tomorrow.

1078
01:02:03,575 --> 01:02:04,576
Ji-yoon.

1079
01:02:06,662 --> 01:02:08,330
Can you pull out of the wedding song?

1080
01:02:08,914 --> 01:02:09,915
What?

1081
01:02:11,375 --> 01:02:14,378
I guess it's too late
to pull out now, isn't it?

1082
01:02:14,461 --> 01:02:15,712
Hmm.

1083
01:02:15,796 --> 01:02:18,674
Yes, I've already agreed to do it.

1084
01:02:18,757 --> 01:02:20,801
It's my best friend's wedding too.

1085
01:02:21,510 --> 01:02:22,886
Why, all of a sudden?

1086
01:02:24,638 --> 01:02:27,391
Well, there's a big sale
at the supermarket tomorrow.

1087
01:02:31,770 --> 01:02:32,771
Oh.

1088
01:02:32,854 --> 01:02:35,357
Should I just tell him now?

1089
01:02:36,650 --> 01:02:38,777
No. Tomorrow.

1090
01:02:38,860 --> 01:02:42,072
So, should we meet after practice then?

1091
01:02:43,407 --> 01:02:44,616
Yes, of course.

1092
01:02:49,746 --> 01:02:50,956
By the way,

1093
01:02:51,039 --> 01:02:55,085
Ms. Choi came by earlier saying
she couldn't reach you when she tried.

1094
01:02:56,295 --> 01:02:57,296
Did you two get to talk?

1095
01:03:00,340 --> 01:03:01,341
Yes.

1096
01:03:02,593 --> 01:03:05,512
What did she call you
during that phone call?

1097
01:03:06,722 --> 01:03:08,265
"Mr. Kang Si-woo"?

1098
01:03:08,348 --> 01:03:10,767
Or was it "Si-woo"?

1099
01:03:11,476 --> 01:03:12,477
-The song…
-The call…

1100
01:03:28,201 --> 01:03:29,536
Ooh! Oh, no!

1101
01:03:50,057 --> 01:03:51,892
-Ji-yoon!
-Yes?

1102
01:03:56,688 --> 01:03:58,357
There aren't any towels in the bathroom.

1103
01:03:58,440 --> 01:04:00,317
Oh. Hang on one sec.

1104
01:04:29,054 --> 01:04:30,263
Do you want to come in?

1105
01:04:30,347 --> 01:04:31,348
Sorry?

1106
01:04:38,563 --> 01:04:39,564
Yes.

1107
01:04:50,992 --> 01:04:53,453
[romantic music playing]

1108
01:05:28,655 --> 01:05:29,990
MISSED CALL
MANAGER CHOI SOO-JIN

1109
01:05:30,073 --> 01:05:31,241
MESSAGE FROM
MANAGER CHOI SOO-JIN

1110
01:05:31,324 --> 01:05:34,077
[Soo-jin] Have you thought about
the favor I asked over the phone?

1111
01:05:34,161 --> 01:05:36,163
[music continues]

1112
01:06:23,043 --> 01:06:24,211
[Hye-ji] You said you wouldn't.

1113
01:06:24,711 --> 01:06:26,254
You told me not to worry!

1114
01:06:26,338 --> 01:06:27,214
[Seong-min] You like her that much?

1115
01:06:27,297 --> 01:06:28,882
[Si-woo] She's too good for me.

1116
01:06:29,424 --> 01:06:31,176
[Soo-jin] Kang Si-woo,
you've changed a lot.

1117
01:06:32,469 --> 01:06:34,596
Tell me.
Something's up with Ji-yoon, right?

1118
01:06:35,347 --> 01:06:37,057
[Hye-ji]
You said his ex-wife was your mentor.

1119
01:06:38,391 --> 01:06:40,227
[Ji-yoon] To be honest, it bothers me.

1120
01:06:40,310 --> 01:06:42,687
It seems that I lied to you.

1121
01:06:43,814 --> 01:06:45,899
[Ga-eul] I want you to stop seeing him.

1122
01:06:45,982 --> 01:06:47,818
[Ji-yoon] Why did you two divorce?

1123
01:06:47,901 --> 01:06:49,402
Whatever the reason,

1124
01:06:49,486 --> 01:06:51,863
is it something
that I'll be able to handle?

